      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: resolve Windows Codex spawn failures for local review runs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `CODEX_BIN` env var support following the existing `GIT_BIN` pattern\n- Add `shell: process.platform === \"win32\"` to both Codex `spawnSync` call sites\n\n## Motivation\n\nOn Windows, npm installs `codex` as `codex.cmd`. Node's `spawnSync` cannot execute `.cmd` files without `shell: true`, causing ENOENT or EINVAL errors when ClawSweeper tries to spawn Codex for review or assist.\n\n## Proof\n\nTested on Windows 11, Node 24.12.0, Codex CLI 0.130.0:\n\n**Before:**\n```\nspawnSync codex ENOENT        (bare \"codex\", no shell)\nspawnSync codex.cmd EINVAL    (CODEX_BIN=codex.cmd, no shell)\n```\n\n**After (CODEX_BIN + shell: true):**\n```\nOpenAI Codex v0.130.0\nworkdir: C:\\Users\\Cameron\\clawd\\openclaw-fork\nmodel: gpt-5.5\nprovider: openai\nsandbox: read-only\n```\nCodex subprocess launches and connects to the API.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `src/clawsweeper.ts` -- `runCodex()` and `runCodexAssist()`: add `CODEX_BIN` env var + `shell: win32`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Windows: ENOENT/EINVAL resolved, Codex subprocess launches\n- [ ] Mac/Linux: no behavioral change (`shell` is false, `CODEX_BIN` defaults to `\"codex\"`)\n",
        "branch": "fix/windows-codex-spawn",
